SAA CEO Vuyani Jarana has resigned, according to a report by Fin24. The report stated that Jarana will leave SAA on 31 August 2019. Jarana, the former head of Vodacom’s enterprise division, was appointed as the new CEO of SAA in August 2017. Jarana was previously chief operating officer at Vodacom before heading up the enterprise division. The latest report stated that he expressed “uncertainty about funding and slow decision making processes” in SAA in his resignation letter.